In[71]:
def clean_numeric(value):
    if pd.isna(value): return np.nan
    if isinstance(value, (int, float)): return float(value)
    value = str(value).strip()
    if value in ['[x]', '..', '.', 'LSVT', '-', '', 'nan', 'None', 'x']: return np.nan
    try: return float(value.replace(',', ''))
    except: return np.nan
In[72]:
def clean_borough_code(code):
    if pd.isna(code): return None
    code = str(code).strip()
    return code if code.startswith('E09') else None
In[73]:
def wide_to_long(df, id_cols, value_name, year_cols):
    df_long = df.melt(id_vars=id_cols, value_vars=year_cols, var_name='year', value_name=value_name)
    df_long['year'] = df_long['year'].astype(int)
    return df_long
In[74]:
def parse_financial_year(fy_string):
    """Convert '2004-05' or '2017-2018' to 2004 or 2017"""
    try:
        return int(str(fy_string).split('-')[0])
    except:
        return None

df_completions_raw = pd.read_excel(files['affordable_completions'], sheet_name='Data', header=0)
fy_cols = [c for c in df_completions_raw.columns if '-' in str(c)]
id_cols_comp = [c for c in df_completions_raw.columns if c not in fy_cols]
col_rename = {}
for col in id_cols_comp:
    col_lower = str(col).lower()
    if 'former' in col_lower or 'old' in col_lower: col_rename[col] = 'old_code'
    elif 'current' in col_lower or 'ons' in col_lower: col_rename[col] = 'borough_code'
    elif 'area' in col_lower or 'name' in col_lower: col_rename[col] = 'borough_name'
df_completions_raw = df_completions_raw.rename(columns=col_rename)
if 'borough_code' in df_completions_raw.columns:
    df_completions_raw['borough_code'] = df_completions_raw['borough_code'].apply(clean_borough_code)
    df_complete = df_completions_raw[df_completions_raw['borough_code'].notna()].copy()
else:
    df_complete = df_completions_raw.merge(borough_lookup, on='borough_name', how='left')
    df_complete = df_complete[df_complete['borough_code'].notna()].copy()
fy_to_year = {fy: parse_financial_year(fy) for fy in fy_cols}
fy_to_year = {k: v for k, v in fy_to_year.items() if v in years}
df_complete = df_complete.rename(columns=fy_to_year)
available_comp_years = [y for y in years if y in df_complete.columns]
df_completions = wide_to_long(df_complete, ['borough_code', 'borough_name'], 'affordable_completions', available_comp_years)
df_completions['affordable_completions'] = df_completions['affordable_completions'].apply(clean_numeric)
df_completions.head()

df_merged = df_merged.sort_values(['borough_code', 'year']).reset_index(drop=True)
for col in ['house_price', 'social_housing_stock', 'vacant_dwellings', 'waiting_list', 'affordability_ratio']:
    if col in df_merged.columns:
        df_merged[f'{col}_change'] = df_merged.groupby('borough_code')[col].diff()
        df_merged[f'{col}_pct_change'] = df_merged.groupby('borough_code')[col].pct_change() * 100
if 'social_rent_weekly' in df_merged.columns:
    df_merged['social_rent_annual'] = df_merged['social_rent_weekly'] * 52
if 'population' in df_merged.columns:
    for col, new_col in [('waiting_list', 'waiting_list_per_1000'), 
                         ('vacant_dwellings', 'vacancies_per_1000'),('social_housing_stock', 'social_stock_per_1000')]:
        if col in df_merged.columns:
            df_merged[new_col] = np.where(df_merged['population'] > 0,
                                          (df_merged[col] / df_merged['population']) * 1000, np.nan)
if 'house_price' in df_merged.columns and 'social_rent_annual' in df_merged.columns:
    df_merged['rent_gap_ratio'] = np.where(df_merged['social_rent_annual'] > 0,
                                            df_merged['house_price'] / df_merged['social_rent_annual'], np.nan)
inner_codes = ['E09000001', 'E09000007', 'E09000012', 'E09000013', 'E09000014',
               'E09000019', 'E09000020', 'E09000022', 'E09000023', 'E09000025', 'E09000028', 'E09000030', 'E09000032', 'E09000033']
df_merged['inner_london'] = df_merged['borough_code'].isin(inner_codes).astype(int)
for lag in [1, 2, 3]:
    df_merged[f'affordability_lag{lag}'] = df_merged.groupby('borough_code')['affordability_ratio'].shift(lag)
print(f'Features created. Total columns: {len(df_merged.columns)}')
print(f'\nMissing values summary:')
missing = df_merged.isnull().sum()
print(missing[missing > 0])

# Time series plots
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(16, 10))

ax = axes[0, 0]
for inner, label, color in [(1, 'Inner', 'coral'), (0, 'Outer', 'steelblue')]:
    data = df_merged[df_merged['inner_london'] == inner].groupby('year')['affordability_ratio'].mean()
    ax.plot(data.index, data.values, marker='o', label=label, color=color)
ax.set_title('Affordability Ratio'); ax.legend(); ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

ax = axes[0, 1]
for inner, label, color in [(1, 'Inner', 'coral'), (0, 'Outer', 'steelblue')]:
    data = df_merged[df_merged['inner_london'] == inner].groupby('year')['house_price'].mean() / 1000
    ax.plot(data.index, data.values, marker='o', label=label, color=color)
ax.set_title('House Prices (k)'); ax.legend(); ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

ax = axes[0, 2]
if 'social_rent_weekly' in df_merged.columns:
    for inner, label, color in [(1, 'Inner', 'coral'), (0, 'Outer', 'steelblue')]:
        data = df_merged[df_merged['inner_london'] == inner].groupby('year')['social_rent_weekly'].mean()
        ax.plot(data.index, data.values, marker='o', label=label, color=color)
ax.set_title('Social Rent (/week)'); ax.legend(); ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plot_config = [('social_housing_stock', 'Social Stock ( )k', 'teal', axes[1,0]),
               ('waiting_list', 'Waiting List ( )k', 'indianred', axes[1,1]),
               ('vacant_dwellings', 'Vacancies ( )k', 'goldenrod', axes[1,2])]

for var, title, color, ax in plot_config:
    if var in df_merged.columns:
        data = df_merged.groupby('year')[var].sum() / 1000
        ax.bar(data.index, data.values, color=color, alpha=0.7)
        ax.set_title(title)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('fig1_trends.png', dpi=150)

# correlation and panel regression
min_year, max_year = df_merged['year'].min(), df_merged['year'].max()
results = []
for code in df_merged['borough_code'].unique():
    bd = df_merged[df_merged['borough_code'] == code]
    first = bd[bd['year'] == min_year]
    last = bd[bd['year'] == max_year]
    if len(first) > 0 and len(last) > 0:
        results.append({
            'borough_code': code,
            'borough_name': bd['borough_name'].iloc[0],
            'inner_london': bd['inner_london'].iloc[0],
            'stock_start': first['social_housing_stock'].values[0],
            'stock_end': last['social_housing_stock'].values[0],
            'afford_start': first['affordability_ratio'].values[0],
            'afford_end': last['affordability_ratio'].values[0]
        })
stock_change = pd.DataFrame(results)
stock_change['stock_change_pct'] = ((stock_change['stock_end'] - stock_change['stock_start']) / stock_change['stock_start']) * 100
stock_change['afford_change'] = stock_change['afford_end'] - stock_change['afford_start']
sc_clean = stock_change.dropna(subset=['stock_change_pct', 'afford_change'])

if len(gent_cols) >= 2:
    df_gent = df_merged.dropna(subset=gent_cols + ['affordability_ratio']).copy()
    print(f'Observations with complete data: {len(df_gent)}')
    if len(df_gent) >= 20:
        scaler_gent = StandardScaler()
        X_gent = scaler_gent.fit_transform(df_gent[gent_cols])
        
        weights = {'house_price_pct_change': 0.4, 'social_housing_stock_pct_change': -0.3,
                   'vacant_dwellings_pct_change': -0.1, 'rent_gap_ratio': 0.2}
        df_gent_scaled = pd.DataFrame(X_gent, columns=gent_cols, index=df_gent.index)
        df_gent['gentrification_index'] = sum(df_gent_scaled[col] * weights.get(col, 0) for col in gent_cols)
        
        pca = PCA(n_components=1)
        df_gent['gentrification_index_pca'] = pca.fit_transform(X_gent)
        print(f'PCA explained variance: {pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]:.1%}')
        print('Gentrification index created')
    else:
        print('Insufficient data after removing NaN')
else:

    df_model = df_gent.dropna(subset=pred_cols + ['affordability_ratio']).copy()
    if len(df_model) >= 50:
        X = df_model[pred_cols]
        y = df_model['affordability_ratio']
        X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)
        models = {'Linear': LinearRegression(),
                  'Random Forest': RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42, max_depth=10),
                  'Gradient Boosting': GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)}
        
        results = []
        for name, model in models.items():
            model.fit(X_train, y_train)
            pred = model.predict(X_test)
            results.append({'Model': name, 'RMSE': np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, pred)), 'R': r2_score(y_test, pred)})
        print(pd.DataFrame(results).round(4).to_string(index=False))
        
        rf = models['Random Forest']
        print('\nFeature Importance:')
        for f, i in zip(pred_cols, rf.feature_importances_):
            print(f'  {f}: {i:.3f}')
    else:
        print(f'Insufficient data: {len(df_model)} rows')
